-- Two Miners Walk Free After New Zealand Mine Explosion, 27 Were Underground
-- B y   R e b e c c a   E v a n s
-- 2010-11-19T06:09:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/two-miners-walk-free-after-new-zealand-mine-explosion-27-were-underground.html
Pike River Coal Chief Executive
Peter Whittall said 27 miners were underground when an explosion
occured at its mine on the West Coast of New Zealand’s South
Island today.  Whittall said there hadn’t been any communication with the
miners and it wasn’t known if the miners were trapped or
sheltering.  The statements were made in a press conference today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rebecca Evans at 
 revans6@bloomberg.net  